casebody.data:
MARSCHALL et al., Appellants, v. EISEN VINEYARD CO., Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 17, 1894.) Action by August Marsehall and others against the Eisen Vineyard Company.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOEP, and PRYOR, JJ.

Rose & Putzel, for appellants., Douglass & Minton, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals denied, with 810 costs. See 28 N. Y. Supp. 62.
